Leslie S. Pachter, D.C. received his Doctorate of Chiropractic Degree in 1988 from Life Chiropractic University, Marietta, Georgia. Dr. Pachter treats patients in the Boca Raton, Deerfield Beach and Delray Beach area. He has been a practicing Chiropractor in Boca Raton, South Florida for over 27 years and resides in Boca Raton with his wife and two sons.
Dr. Pachter is a Certified Boca Raton Chiropractic Sports Physician as well as a Certified Personal Trainer, making him an excellent resource for on-going chiropractic treatments Boca Raton and wellness care involving proper nutrition, posture and exercise programs. His commitment to spreading the philosophy, science, and art of chiropractic has helped reduce pain in thousands of patients and helped them achieve better health and improve the quality of their lives.
Dr. Pachter strives to get you out of pain, restore range of motion and strengthen the area surrounding your injury. All patients can be assured of Dr. Pachter's expertise, time and attention towards their care. Dr. Pachter continues to take seminars and pursue clinical excellence by keeping up with any information that might be helpful to the overall health of his patients. Whether you've been a life-long chiropractic patient focused on whole body wellness or you are a potential new patient wondering if chiropractic treatment might be able to relieve pain you are experiencing, Dr. Leslie Pachter, an experienced chiropractor in West Boca welcomes your questions. Dr. Joe was born and raised in Kansas City, MO. and Chattanooga, TN. He has two sisters and a brother. He grew up playing soccer, baseball, basketball, track and field, springboard diving, and cross country running. Although he didn't begin until his sophomore year, he became an accomplished football kicker and punter, with a personal best of a 54 yard field goal and a 52 yard punting average. In addition, he claims his 289 bowling score and 190 league average as some of his proudest "sporting" memories. He also played symphonic and jazz trumpet for 13 yrs. and toured for a summer with the Cavaliers drum and bugle corps. The Cavalier's placed 3rd in the world that year. And if that wasn't enough, he was a Boy Scout for 10 yrs. in which he worked as summer camp counselor for two years and earned the Eagle Scout Award. As you can imagine Mrs. Coffman, was the original "soccer mom".
Right out of school, Dr. Joe had the honor to practice with his father for4 yrs. before having the opportunity to also learn from his father-in-law for over a year. He states that during his time mentoring with his fathers, he had the joy and valuable experience to care for everyone from infants to 98 year olds; from quadriplegics to professional athletes.
Dr. Joe is the only doctor in South Florida who is certified in the SpineCor scoliosis bracing system. He has a passion and sympathy for those suffering with scoliosis and continues to develop not only the SpineCor program but also specific chiropractic rehab protocols to further help with these and other complicated spinal problems.
He also enjoys seeking a variety post-graduate education in "motor vehicle injury management" to better care for those involved in auto accidents. …including diagnosis and management of concussions, disc herniations, and spinal ligament injuries, and MRI interpretation.

A South Florida native, Dr. Angel Ares was raised in Miami and received a Bachelor's in Biology from Florida International University's Honors College. He only temporarily left South Florida to attend Chiropractic College at Palmer's, Port Orange campus and returned to join the team at County Line Chiropractic.
Dr. Angel Ares hopes to improve the quality of life within the South Florida Community, not only by using the finest clinical techniques with his patients, but by also translating the best information into simple concepts to improve health.
Dr. Angel Ares has had a fascination with biology since childhood, and learned to appreciate the complexity and beauty of the human body. Chiropractic became a clear choice as a health profession with its ability to focus on the cause of a disease, rather than the masking of the symptoms.
In his career, Dr. Angel Ares developed his goal of not only helping people but also ensuring that they understand their condition and treatment.
Outside the office, Dr. Angel Ares' hobbies include swimming, cycling, camping and playing video games. Always looking for an outdoor activity, Dr. Angel Ares is a member of local Jeep clubs and enjoys rock crawling.

Dr. Amir Hajisafari has been helping to educate and treat people in the South Florida community as a team member of County Line Chiropractic Medical and Rehab for over fifteen years. Prior to becoming a licensed chiropractor, Dr. Hajisafari worked as a research assistant for the University of Miami.
Dr. Hajisafari specializes in various areas of spinal-related pain in the neck and back, extremity numbness and tingling, headaches, Carpal Tunnel Syndrome, Fibromyalgia, and sports injuries.
Dr. Hajisafari earned a Bachelors of Science in Biology from Concordia University in Montreal, Quebec and then continued his chiropractic studies at Life University in Atlanta, Georgia. In his participation of continuous education, Dr. Hajisafari has completed specialty courses in craniosacral techniques, extremity adjustments, and various impairments.
Dr. Hajisafari lives locally with his wife and is fluent in English, Farsi (Persian), and French. He enjoys basketball, running, life science and participating in triathlons.

About: Elan Schrier, DC, knew he was going to spend his life healing the people of Delray Beach, Florida, ever since he was 12 years old. He used to have debilitating migraines and trouble sleeping, but that all changed once he saw a chiropractor for the first time. After the first adjustment, he began to sleep better, and his migraines went away. It was at this moment that he realized his passion was to provide this same healing relief to the community. He studied at Palmer College of Chiropractic in Daytona Beach, Florida, where he earned his degree in Chiropractic. During this time, he learned about many techniques, most notably, those associated with upper cervical care. He found these to be the most precise, results-driven method of treatment to share with his patients. Best of all, this approach required no twisting of the head or cracking of the spine. He specializes in treating: Sciatica Whiplash Fibromyalgia Lower-back pain TMJ Scoliosis Headaches Dr. Elan is a lifelong learner who dedicates himself to staying abreast with the latest techniques in both chiropractic and upper cervical care. Today, he is the head of Schrier Family Chiropractic where he uses his talent to heal the people of Delray Beach, Florida, and the surrounding areas.

Dr. Brandon J. Hochman DC is a Chiropractor with 15 years' experience treating patients.  Dr. Hochman credits his career path with being mentored by being treated and mentored by some of the most highly skilled and successful chiropractors in the industry.  He first was introduced to treatments as a young athlete and his interest in the profession peaked while fulfilling an internship while attending Rutgers University in New Jersey.  As a student athlete at Rutgers, Dr. Hochman competed in both baseball and for the nationally ranked soccer team.  After graduation, he attended Life University in Marietta, Georgia and received his Doctorate of Chiropractic degree.  Dr. Hochman then started his career with the well-known practice Georgia Spinal Health and Wellness.  He later moved to Florida where he became the managing director of a large clinic for a couple years before partnering with Dr. Lawrence Weiner DC at Med Plus Centers.  Dr. Hochman is certified in Manipulation Under Anesthesia and was one of the lead instructors of the technique for two different universities.  Dr. Hochman is also certified in Muscle Activation Techniques, in which only a handful of chiropractors are trained in worldwide.  He and Dr. Weiner are also the official Chiropractors of Bommarito Performance Centers, a top 5 nationally ranked training center for elite high school, college and professional athletes.

Dr. Wuilliam Soris is the dedicated owner of Parkway Chiropractic and Rehab in Florida, where he brings a personal understanding of pain recovery and healing. His journey into chiropractic care began after a series of sports injuries from playing tennis left him struggling with chronic lower back pain and sharp, electric-like sensations down his legs. Traditional treatments didnt work for him, and it wasnt until he tried chiropractic care that he found lasting relief. This life-changing experience inspired him to become a chiropractor and help others overcome pain and live healthier, more active lives.Born and raised in Havana, Cuba, Dr. Soris moved to Miami with a clear vision to pursue his passion for health and wellness. He earned his degree in Exercise and Sports Science from the University of (UCCFD), then went on to study at Palmer College of Chiropractic, the worlds leading chiropractic school. It was there he refined his skills and developed his holistic approach to healthcare, learning from some of the top experts in the field.Dr. Soris believes that every person has an innate ability to heal and that optimal health begins with a well-functioning nervous system. He is dedicated to helping his patients unlock their full healing potential through chiropractic care that focuses on spinal health, pain relief, and overall wellness. Dr. Soris is bilingual in English and Spanish, which allows him to connect more deeply with the local Hispanic community and provide care in both languages. His ability to speak both languages helps him build stronger relationships and ensures that more people can access the care they need.Outside of his practice, Dr. Soris enjoys spending quality time with his family, playing tennis, and staying active with pickleball.

Dr. Wong is a chiropractic physician that emphasizes educating his patients to understand the power of healing from within. With the proper explanation of symptoms and treatment, his focus is to persuade patients to take a more active role in their health. He loves to see patients reach their health goals and live a life without boundaries.After receiving a Bachelor of Science degree in Marketing from the University of Florida he worked as a healthcare consultant in the health informatics sector. As a consultant, he was exposed to how healthcare systems approached sickness and did not understand how so many fell into bad health. Identifying that current health protocol only prolonged the inevitable heath crisis that so many patients quickly approached he wondered what education was being provided to patients to prevent disease. He was fortunate enough to start working with chiropractors at conferences where he discovered their unique and inspiring way of treating illness and more importantly the prevention of illness. He quickly sought care for himself and his family. He fell in love with the art, science, and philosophy of chiropractic. Wanting to do more he decided to go back to school and pursue his doctorate at Palmer College of Chiropractic in Port Orange, FL. When not in the office, he and his wife Michelle, enjoy encouraging their two sons Marcial and Matteo to seek out adventure in their lives.

About: Dr. Michael W. Mathesie, has been practicing in Coral Springs, FL for over 36 years.  During this time he has attained two board certifications; one from the American Chiropractic Rehabilitation Board (DACRB) and the other from the American Board of Forensic Professionals (DABFP); both are recognized specialty boards of the American Chiropractic Association.  Dr. Mathesie has been awarded the Sports Chiropractor of the Year Award in 2000 and the Broward County Chiropractor of the Year in 2008 from his peers.  The ACA selected him to serve on their clinical documentation committee, whereby that committee edits the ACA clinical documentation manual.  They have also selected him to serve on the Ethics Committee. He has served as a board examiner for the Florida Board of Chiropractic Medicine from 1995 to 2008 and also serves as an NBCE Part IV examiner.  He was approved by the secretary of state as an Ombudsman for AHCA.  Two Governors have appointed him to the Florida Board of Athletic Training and the Florida Board of Chiropractic Medicine where he has served as chairman.  He has lectured for the profession in topics including laser therapy certification, sports injuries, rehabilitation, laws and rules, documentation, record keeping and coding, risk management, ethics and boundaries, and prevention of medical errors. Dr. Michael Piccirillo was inspired to become a physician at a young age when injuries to his throwing shoulder threatened his ability to play baseball.  After seeing multiple doctors for his injury, it seemed the only option was rotator cuff surgery.  Desperate for an alternative, he sought out his chiropractor who had provided holistic care for his entire family. After a thorough examination his chiropractor offered this simple and reassuring suggestion, "Give me six weeks, worst case scenario is you don't get better and you have surgery."  Reassured and trusting of his doctors prescribed care, he began therapy.  After the first treatment there was a noticeable decrease in pain levels.  After two weeks of consistent treatment, Dr. P was able to throw lightly.  Four weeks after that, he returned to baseball full-time, pain free, and throwing harder than he had before the injury occurred.  This inspired a passion and sparked a desire for Dr. P to pursue a career in Chiropractic Medicine.
Dr. P began his journey toward helping others as a personal trainer at age 18.  Over the 10 plus years in the fitness industry he earned multiple advanced level training certifications in the areas of fitness and nutrition to better serve his clientele.  He attended the University of Bridgeport College of Chiropractic where he earned his Doctorate of Chiropractic.  Dr. P is a Board Certified Chiropractic Physician in the state of Florida.  Since graduation he has continued to advance his knowledge and understanding of the human body and physical medicine through multiple post-doctoral education and technique specific certifications.  These courses include Graston Technique Level 1, Functional and Kinetic Treatment with Rehab (FAKTR), RockTape Functional Movement Therapy Level 1 and 2, multiple Kinesotape application courses, and McKenzie's Mechanical Diagnosis and Therapy (MDT).  He believes these techniques and experiences prior to obtaining his D.C. help him serve his patients optimally.

Dr. Alexander Zuriarrain was born and raised in Miami, FL, where he began his accomplished academic career at the prestigious Belen Jesuit Preparatory School. During his formative years, at Belen Jesuit, he developed a passion for helping others and solidified his desire to pursue a career as a physician. Dr. Zuriarrain, known by his patients as Dr. Z, was awarded a full scholarship, for his skills as a leader, to North Carolina State University, as a Park Scholar. He went on to obtain his medical degree at Ponce School of Medicine, where he perfected his abilityto treat patients fluently in both English and Spanish. While in medical school, he focused his efforts on a career as a surgeon and subsequently completed, with distinction, a five-year residency program in general surgery at the University of New Mexico in Albuquerque, NM. Afterwards, he obtained board certification from the American Board of Surgery. His passion for perfectionism and attention to detail led him to complete three years of additional residency training in plastic and reconstructive surgery at the world-renowned Cleveland Clinic Florida. While at the Cleveland Clinic, he sharpened his skills as an aesthetic plastic surgeon. He conducted numerous research projects and presented his findings at a host of medical conferences sponsored by the American Society for Aesthetic Plastic Surgery; the American Society of Plastic Surgeons and the Southeastern Society of Plastic and Reconstructive Surgeons, among others. Dr. Z then reached the highest peak of his surgical education by performing a one-year fellowship with the American Academy of Cosmetic Surgery. He subsequently got the highest score on the American Board of Cosmetic Surgery examination of which he now serves as a board examiner. He also became board certified by the American Board of Facial Cosmetic Surgery due to his broad experience in facial plastic surgery. This makes Dr. Z a QUADRUPLE board-certified surgeon. Dr. Z specializes in aesthetic procedures of the face and body including facelift, eyelid surgery, rhinoplasty, breast augmentation and reduction, abdominoplasty, gluteal augmentation with fat transfer, vaginal rejuvenation, and liposuction, among others. He has won many awards and has a multitude of publications in peer-reviewed journals. He is an active member of several professional organizations and currently holds an active medical license in the state of Florida. He also has active privileges at some of South Florida's most reputable hospitals. His extensive training grants him the ability to provide his patients with excellent outcomes in an environment focused on patient safety. He is well-known for his surgical talent in the operating room, which leads to beautiful surgical results. His patients enjoy his warm and caring personality and appreciate his professional bedside manner.

He subsequently attended Harvard Medical School, where he was among a handful of students selected to pursue a joint degree with Harvard Business School. About:
Dr. Bernard Cohen is a recognized authority in the field of hair loss and hair restoration; and is certified by the American Board of Dermatology and the American Board of Hair Restoration Surgery. Since 1974, he's maintained a practice in Miami and Coral Gables, while actively serving on the pro bono teaching faculty at University of Miami, School of Medicine, Department of Dermatology. Within that department, Dr. Cohen holds the title of Clinical Professor-Voluntary Faculty, and was the Department's former Director of Surgical Training. He's received multiple awards for his dedicated service to the residency-training program.
Born and educated in Pennsylvania, Dr. Cohen earned his M.D. degree from Columbia University, College of Physicians & Surgeons. He performed his dermatology training at New York University's Skin & Cancer Hospital, where he was chief resident. He then served on the faculty of NYU Medical School while serving as Chief of Dermatology at West Point Military Academy.
Since 2000, Dr. Cohen has been listed annually in Woodward and White's "Best Doctors in America" and Castle Connolly's "America's Top Doctors." He is a Fellow of the American Academy of Dermatology and an active member of the International Society of Hair Restoration Surgery (ISHRS) – a medical society of over 1000 members, dedicated to disorders of hair loss and their treatment. In 2010 he was awarded the society's highest honor — the "Platinum Follicle" for outstanding achievement in hair science and research.
Dr. Cohen has written multiple medical textbook chapters, most recently in Stough & Haber's "Hair Restoration" and Unger & Shapiro's "Hair Transplantation" the foremost textbook on the subject of hair. He has authored over 20 scientific articles and commentaries in the medical and surgical literature, and has lectured to more than 25 different medical and surgical societies throughout the world. Dr. Cohen has been awarded 3 US and 12 international patents for medical devices that he personally invented.
One of Dr. Cohen's most significant contributions to the field of hair science has been a new technology called Cross Section Trichometry (CST). CST has received critical acclaim in human hair research, and has been adapted (as the HairCheck device) for use in the medical community at large. He has recently joined Hevia Cosmetic Dermatology, and is available for hair loss consultations several days a week.

About:
Dr. Bradford W. Lee is an oculofacial plastic and reconstructive surgeon, a board-certified ophthalmologist, and one of only 800 members of the prestigious American Society of Ophthalmic Plastic and Reconstructive Surgery (ASOPRS). From 2015-2021, he was a professor at the Bascom Palmer Eye Institute at the University of Miami, ranked the #1 eye hospital in the USA for the past 18 years, and is currently Voluntary Faculty where he continues to advance the department's academic mission. In June 2021, he moved back to his native Hawaii to found Oculofacial Plastic Surgery of Hawaii.
Dr. Lee graduated from Iolani school and went on to Harvard University where he graduated magna cum laude and Phi Beta Kappa. The recipient of Harvard's Frank Knox Memorial Fellowship, he pursued a master's degree in health policy, planning, and financing at the London School of Economics, where he graduated with high honors and was awarded the Brian Abel Smith Prize.
He attended Stanford University for medical school, completed his ophthalmology residency at Bascom Palmer Eye Institute, and went on to complete a 2-year oculoplastics fellowship with renowned surgeons Dr. Don Kikkawa and Dr. Bobby Korn at University of California San Diego's Shiley Eye Institute. During fellowship, he had the opportunity to work with some of the finest facial plastic surgeons and cosmetic dermatologists throughout Southern California and across the country. He was a two-time recipient of the Outstanding Teaching Award at UCSD, received the 2016 Marvin L. Quickert Prize from ASOPRS for outstanding research on thyroid eye disease, and was a 2020 recipient of the Achievement Award from the American Academy of Ophthalmology. He has served on the program committee for the American Academy of Ophthalmology and ASOPRS meetings.
Dr. Lee has given over 150 lectures at national and international meetings, including the American Academy of Ophthalmology (AAO), ASOPRS, International Thyroid Eye Disease Society, Inter-American Course in Clinical Ophthalmology, American Academy of Cosmetic Surgery, Vegas Cosmetic Surgery, Cosmetic Surgery Forum, and regional meetings in Asia, South America, Europe, the Caribbean, and the Middle East.
He is passionate about global ophthalmology and advancing the field of oculoplastics abroad. In this capacity, he has trained international oculoplastics fellows, served as faculty with Orbis International aboard the flying eye hospital, collaborated on international research, and worked as a Visiting Consultant for the Ministry of Health of the United Arab Emirates, teaching and performing oculoplastic surgery in Dubai on various occasions.
Outside of work, he enjoys playing the piano and cello, tennis, kayaking, skiing, hiking, and traveling. He is fluent in English and Spanish, and speaks limited French and Mandarin. He sees patients in Honolulu (Oahu), Wailuku and Kihei (Maui), and Palm Beach Gardens (Florida).

Dr. Glenn M. Charles was born in Buffalo, New York, and raised in the suburbs of Detroit, Michigan. After receiving his undergraduate degree from Michigan State University he obtained his medical degree from Nova Southeastern University School of medicine in North Miami Beach, Fl. Dr. Charles then completed an internship and residency at Michigan State University affiliated hospitals before acting as the primary physician trainer in hair transplant surgery for a large hair transplant organization from 1997-1999. He opened his boutique private practice, Charles Medical Group in 1999.
Dr. Charles is the past President and a current Diplomat of the American Board of Hair Restoration Surgery and sat on their Surgery Examination Committee for eight years.
Dr. Charles is active in several medical societies including The International Society of Hair Restoration Surgery (ISHRS) and The International Alliance of Hair Restoration Surgery (IAHRS).

About:
Dr. Andrea Hass, or Dr. A as her patients fondly call her, has been a fixture of the Palm Beach Plastic Surgery scene for more than 21 years. First trained as an ophthalmologist, she is fellowship trained in Oculoplastic Surgery, which is cosmetic and reconstructive eyelid surgery.
"I can vividly remember the day I discovered oculoplastic surgery as the focus of my career in medicine. I had already decided to pursue ophthalmology as my medical specialty, and I was spending a month at Wills Eye Hospital. My 'ah-ha' moment came when watching my future mentor, Dr. Joseph Flanagan, reconstruct an eyelid. Right then I knew that oculoplastics offered me the perfect combination of a challenging surgical specialty that also appealed to my creative and artistic side. To this day, I feel fortunate to have a satisfying career that I thoroughly enjoy."
Her many patients who have been coming to her for as long as 20 years and have become friends over the years describe her as: "Warm, friendly, poised and elegant". Their loyalty to her for her exact techniques and the beautiful results she provides have allowed them to age gracefully without looking odd or over done.
Eight Things to Know About Dr. Andrea Hass (Dr. A)
1. Dr A studied bioengineering at the University of Pennsylvania because she enjoyed the problem solving approach to learning. Cosmetic eyelid, brow lift surgeries and facial injectables are similarly problem focused.
2. Internship near her sister in Connecticut became her own "Grey's Anatomy" when she met her husband, Dr. Brian Hass.
3. Oculoplastic Surgery (specialized plastic surgery of the eyes) is so unique and competitive, only about 30 doctors are trained each year.
4. Dr A performs about 25 times the number of eyelid surgeries as the typical busy cosmetic plastic surgeon.
5. Dr A is known for being thorough and patient during consults as well as thoughtful and precise in the OR. She keeps up with the latest in cosmetic practices and has always been committed to learning new skills and only bringing the best options to the practice. If she wouldn't have a procedure done to herself, family or staff, she won't offer it to her patients.
6. Both patients and other doctors acknowledge that she is among the best at what she does. In fact, other plastic surgeons send her their challenging eyelid cases to perform. These factors are tops among reasons why she has long been the "go to" person for cosmetic eyelid surgery as well as facial injectables.
7. Dr A is in the top 1% of the busiest injectors for both Botox and facial fillers. This is a result of nearly 20 years as an injector as well as her beautiful results.
8. Through her team effort with Dr Brian Hass for facelifts, her patients get the best of both worlds to meet their cosmetic needs in a warm, natural, consistent and caring fashion. In fact, if someone in the Palm Beach area isn't already her patient, in all likelihood, they have friends who are.

Dr. Gary L. Marder is the medical director of Marder Dermatology, and Skin Cancer Center located in Port Saint Lucie and Okeechobee, Florida. Dr. Marder is an Assistant Clinical Professor of Dermatology and Dermatologic Surgery at three different medical schools, S.E.C.O.M./Nova University in Fort Lauderdale, Florida, L.E.C.O.M. in Bradenton, Florida, and Des Moines University in Des Moines, Iowa. Dr. Marder has practiced in Florida since 1983 and has a very unique practice. Dr. Marder not only specializes in dermatology, but he sub-specializes in cosmetic surgery, reconstructive surgery for skin cancers, and is one of the only dermatologists in the state of Florida who is trained and state licensed to treat different skin cancers with radiation therapy in the office. Utilizing radiation therapy, Dr. Marder has been able to save many patients from surgery, as well as in preserving the ears, eyelids, nose, and lips from surgical disfigurement and scarring. To Dr. Marder, the patient's cosmetic outcome is as much as an important factor as insuring that the patient has an excellent curable surgical outcome.
Dr. Marder also specializes in and performs the following cosmetic procedures: BOTOXÂ® Cosmetic, Restylaneâ„¢, Sculptraâ„¢, eye-lifts, mini face-lifts, laser surgery for the removal of superficial and deep wrinkles, chemical peels, hair removal, spider and varicose veins, as well as treating diseases of the skin, hair, and nails. Dr. Marder travels extensively all over the world to keep up with the latest innovations in the field of dermatology and cosmetic surgery. Dr. Marder has patients who travel from as far south as Key West, from the west coast of Florida, and from northern Florida. Dr. Marder also has a keen interest in treating atopic dermatitis in patients through use of finding the cause of disease by performing inhalant and food allergy testing. Dr. Marder is Board Certified and is a member of the American Academy of Dermatology, American Society of Dermatologic Surgery, Dermatologic Radiation Therapy Society, Florida Society of Dermatologic Surgery, Florida Dermatology Society, American Osteopathic College of Dermatology, American Osteopathic Association, and the International Society of Dermatologic Surgeons.

Dr. Man is board-certified in plastic and reconstructive surgery and certified by the American Board of Plastic Surgery. His professional affiliations include: Member, American Society of Plastic Surgeons, American Society Aesthetic Plastic Surgeons, American Medical Association, Florida Medical Association, Lipolysis Society of North America, and Palm Beach County Society of Plastic and Reconstructive Surgeons, among others. He is well known as one of the premier plastic surgeons in South Florida for his breakthrough procedures and treatment methods, and has patients across the country who travel miles to undergo his treatments.
Dr. Man has developed specific treatments for both men and women. He is the creator of the renowned "Man Lift" a facelift which takes into account the differences between men and women when it comes to facial structure and skin quality, and uses a special technique for men's and women's facelifts to prevent ears from dropping â€“ a technique that is now the gold standard for facelifts.
Dr. Man has also developed a number of different proprietary procedures such as an improved gynecomastia procedure for male breast reduction; a specialized liposuction method; and injections that utilize platelet rich plasma for faster healing after procedures. He also designed the ART Bed, which allows for better plastic surgery results by allowing him to operate on a patient that is not fully flat â€“ thus taking into account the effect of gravity on the body.
Dr. Man is also known for his Skin Rejuvenation Peel which is a non-surgical procedure that takes 20 years off of your appearance and lasts about 20 years; the unsurpassed DM|MD skin rejuvenation treatment which is a non-surgical treatment with incredible results; and the TriLift which combines a number of non-surgical techniques to achieve the facelift effect.
Additionally, Dr. Man holds a patent for an implantable homing device to help locate missing children, foreign diplomats and Alzheimer's patients. He never stops looking for ways to improve his practice, his patients, and his world.

Dr. DeRosa is a Double Board Certified Facial Plastic Surgeon with private practices in Boston, Massachusetts and Palm Beach, Florida. She is also an Assistant Professor of Surgery at Harvard Medical School. Born and raised in upstate New York Dr. DeRosa received her MS in Biology at the University of Virginia and her MD at the SYNU of Buffalo, graduating top of her class. She then proceeded to receive her surgical training at Boston University Medical School and sought-after Fellowship training at the University of Chicago under mentorship of Dr. Dean Toriumi, the most acclaimed Facial Plastic Surgeon in the world. She started practicing in 2005 and entered private practice in 2013, successfully combining private practice and her academic career ever since.She comes from a family of Medical Doctors (fourteen of them, to be exact), being a third-generation physician herself. Since childhood, Jaimie was fascinated with medicine and went with her grandfather when he would make house calls to see his patients in New Jersey. She also loved to visit her father's ophthalmological operating room in upstate New York and she attributes her lifelong desire to heal and make people's lives better to those early experiences.
Dr. DeRosa has also been interested in architecture and interior design throughout most of her life, clipping interesting articles and pictures from Architectural Digest and following her favorite designer, Victoria Hagen throughout college until today. It is by no coincidence that these two lifelong passions have contributed to her decision to become a Facial Plastic Surgeon. She is a specialist, with an artistic eye and impeccable technical skill which work together to achieve outstanding cosmetic outcomes. Dr. DeRosa's love of medicine and compassionate care have resulted in the highest level of patient satisfaction and loyalty.
Dr. DeRosa is also an accomplished scientist and researcher who has written over a hundred peer-reviewed articles and has contributed her writings to many books. She also makes presentations all over the world and is a highly regarded expert speaker in the field of Facial Plastic Surgery. Dr. DeRosa has won the prestigious " Best of Boston- Top Doctor for Facial Plastic Surgery" awarded by Boston Magazine for the year of 2025.

Dr. Rami GhuraniThrough that unique experience he had the opportunity to have first hand exposure of treating patients with multiple facial deformities through the Dept. of Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery. This sparked a long journey which lead Dr. Ghurani with his dental background to complete his surgical training in the field of Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery (OMFS), which included obtaining his medical degree at The University of Miami School of Medicine. It was that period that opened his eyes to the exciting world of Plastic and Reconstructive Surgery.
After completing his OMFS training Dr. Ghurani set out on a path to qualify for proper training and certification in Plastic and Reconstructive Surgery. That was achieved by completing further training in General Surgery after which he matriculated at the University of South Florida College of Medicine Plastic Surgery Residency program under the directorship of David J. Smith Jr., MD. Prior to starting the plastic surgery residency at USF he had the opportunity to spend a year long fellowship with world renowned Plastic Surgeon Dr. S. A. Wolfe that specializes in Craniofacial Surgery. After completing his training, Dr. Ghurani stayed as faculty at USF school of medicine, where he enjoyed a full scope plastic surgery practice. The wealth of experience that Dr. Ghurani acquired by dealing with complex head and neck, and breast reconstruction placed him at a unique advantage to have the skills needed to perform aesthetic surgery of the face and body.
At the completion of his plastic surgery training Dr. Ghurani was asked to stay on faculty as Assistant Professor of Surgery at USF division of Plastic Surgery. Due to the unique partnership between USF and Moffit Cancer Center he was able to accumulate a vast experience in reconstructive surgery of the breast amongst other oncologic reconstruction. The high volume opportunity at USF helped solidify his abilities and comfort level in plastic surgery of the face and body.
Dr. Ghurani's comfortable, relaxed manner puts patients at ease.Dr. Ghurani's comfortable, relaxed manner puts patients at ease. He has seen that enhancing a person's appearance can result in an improvement in both self-esteem and confidence, and he feels privileged to be able to play a part in this transformation. Through his strong training he has acquired vast surgical skills that place him at an advantage when it comes to the field of aesthetic plastic surgery and hence he offers full scope of aesthetic and reconstructive plastic surgery procedures, including invasive and non invasive facial and body rejuvenation.
Aesthetic Plastic Surgery has continued to evolve over the years. When seeking aesthetic enhancement we encourage you to research the qualifications of your Surgeon. Qualified plastic surgeons are certified by the American Board of Plastic Surgery and endorsed by the American Society of Plastic Surgeons.
At your consultation Dr. Ghurani will listen closely to your concerns and expectations. We will develop a comprehensive aesthetic package designed especially for you. Our approach will focus on your concerns and set you on your way towards a journey of rejuvenation. In this practice it is our aim to design a regiment that will address all aspects of your beauty

C. Roberto Palma, MD is a graduate of Harvard Medical School and did his residency in Plastic Surgery at Stanford University. He has been in private practice in Ft. Lauderdale since 1981. He has been selected by his peers for 15 years in a row to be included in Castle Connolly's List of "America's Top Doctors", as well as the Consumer's Research Council of America "Guide to America's Top Surgeons". In addition to his surgical skills and experience, Dr. Palma is considered an expert in Cosmetic Medicine or non-surgical procedures to make patients look younger. He is one of the most experienced users of Paralyzing agents such as Botox, Dysport and Xeomin as well as Filler/Volumizers such as Restylane, Perlane, Juvaderm, Radiesse, Sculptra, Voluma and other FDA approved products.
Over the years, Dr. Palma's practice has focused more and more on Aesthetic (Cosmetic) Surgery. In the last decade he introduced into his practice the SimpleLIFT, an innovative technique of face/neck lifting which evolved over his many years of experience in the field. In the last couple years he has added what he calls "Butterfly Suspension" to the SimpleLIFT, a technique of tightening the deeper structures of the cheeks and neck, such as muscles and fascia, which results in finer scars as well as more natural-looking and more long-lasting results. The procedure, usually performed under local anesthesia, offers dramatic results with significantly reduced cost and "downtime".

Vishtasb Broumand, DMD, MD graduated from the University Of Florida College Of Dentistry in 1997 and subsequently from the University Of Miami School Of Medicine in 2000. He completed his postdoctoral residency training in Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery along with an additional year of General Surgery at the University of Miami/ Jackson Memorial Hospital in 2003. Since then he also completed a fellowship in Head and Neck Tumor and Reconstructive Surgery under the mentorship of Dr. Robert E. Marx at the University of Miami in 2005.
He served as Assistant Professor of Clinical Surgery in the University of Miami School of Medicine Division of Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery in Miami, FL from 2005 to 2006 and was in private practice from 2006 to 2012 upon his full time return to the University of Miami School of Medicine Division of Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery.
He served as Associate Professor in the University of Miami School of Medicine Division of Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery from 5/2012 to 10/2014 and remains as adjunct faculty at the University of Florida College of Dentistry Department of Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery since 7/2010. He has now returned to the full time private practice of Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery.
Dr. Broumand spent 2 years in private practice in Boca Raton, FL and 4 years in Daytona Beach, FL from 2005 to 2011 and regularly participates in medical rescue missions and relief efforts. While in private practice he was also involved in extensive repair of craniofacial congenital and acquired deformities of adults and children through several non-profit foundations â€œMission Rescateâ€ and â€œOperation Changing Livesâ€ in the Dominican Republic and Haiti and other medically underserved areas.
After the devastating earthquake in Haiti in January 2010, Dr. Broumand closed his private practice on 2 occasions and chartered a private plane to the Dominican Republic and put together a group of 8 doctors for immediate emergency relief. Once in the DR they were forced to drive 12 hours to Port Au Prince from Santa Domingo along rough terrain. While in Haiti, Dr Broumand and his group worked out of the University of Miami tent hospital constructed by Project Medishare to provide relief effort.
Since the devastating earthquakes he has led two mission trips to Port Au Prince in 2010 and 2011, and in 2010 he was able to bring a young lady with a large Ossifying Fibroma of 15 years duration from Haiti to Daytona Beach, FL for medical and surgical treatment. He was able to fund her entire travel and stay in the USA through his foundation, and Halifax Medical Center generously funded her entire surgery and hospital stay in exchange for the 50 years of service that his partners Dr.â€™s Phillip Fleuchaus and Richard Gaines had given the community.
The Patient, Ms. Lorrette Pierre, underwent surgical and dental rehabilitation and returned to Haiti, he was able to see her during one of his yearly visits to the DR in which he accompanies dental students from the University of FL teaching them exodontia and oral surgery in rural areas in the DR.
He devotes most of his clinical practice to comprehensive treatment of trauma and tumor related facial reconstructive surgery, as well as surgical correction of TMJ disorders and obstructive sleep apnea (OSA) and orthognathic surgical correction of craniofacial deformities and placement of all-on-four and zygomatic dental implants and is also involved in extensive clinical research involving Bisphosphonate Induced Osteonecrosis of the Jaws (BIONJ).

Dr. Fine's college education began at Long Island University, Brooklyn College of Pharmacy, where he earned a Bachelor of Science degree and became a member of Rho Chi, the academic honor society for pharmaceutical students. Dr. Fine served in the U.S. Navy, where he was on active duty from 1971-1973 and rose to the rank of lieutenant commander. Since 1976, Dr. Fine has operated a private practice of plastic and reconstructive surgery in the South Florida area. His current practice in Pembroke Pines, Florida, offers the full range of cosmetic surgeries such as face-lifts, breast augmentation, breast lifts and reductions, eyelid procedures, tummy tucks, and liposuction. Dr. Fine also offers comprehensive treatment for skin cancer, including reconstructive procedures. When not seeing patients in his private practice, he serves as the chief of staff at Memorial Hospital Miramar.

In 2011, Maryland Governor Martin O'Malley appointed Dr. Singh to be the only plastic surgeon on the Board of Physicians. The medical board is responsible for protecting public health through efficient licensure, effective discipline, and regulatory promulgation. Dr. Singh was very active in reforming the board's operations, and in 2014, the Governor promoted him to Chair of the medical board for an additional two-year term.Most recently, Dr. Singh worked as Chief and Medical Director of Plastic Surgery at Anne Arundel Medical Center in Annapolis. Previously, he held faculty appointments at both the University of Maryland School of Medicine and Johns Hopkins Medicine.Dr. Singh specializes in advanced reconstruction after cancer surgery, including microvascular flap breast reconstruction and Mohs reconstruction of the face. He also performs body-contouring procedures after massive weight loss and aesthetic surgery of the face, breast and body. His areas of research include wound healing, negative pressure therapy, and vascularized composite allotransplantation.With dozens of peer-reviewed articles, book chapters and other publications to his name, Dr. Singh is an expert and national leader in his specialty. His recent publications in Plastic and Reconstructive Surgery and International Wound Journal cover topics such as the latest techniques for breast reconstruction as well as the benefits of closed incision negative pressure dressings. His research helps improve outcomes for patients, both functionally and aesthetically. He has also served as a peer reviewer for numerous journals, including the Journal of the American College of Surgery and Nature - Scientific Reports.Dr. Singh has given hundreds of lectures and presentations locally, across the country, and internationally, furthering the knowledge and skills of plastic surgeons world-wide. He is a member of the American Association of Plastic Surgeons and American Society of Plastic Surgeons, where he leads multiple committees.Dr. Singh has also used his surgical skills to give back through numerous humanitarian mission trips to Thailand, Uganda, Vietnam, and many other countries. During these trips, he has performed cleft lip and palate corrections on hundreds of children.

ABOUT ME
Sharon McQuillan, MD is a board-certified physician specializing in integrative, regenerative, and aesthetic medicine. She graduated from The Ohio State University School of Medicine and is a member of Alpha Omega Alpha Medical Honors Society. As a board-certified family practitioner, she focused on preventive medicine, diet and exercise, bio-identical hormone replacement, and the mind-body connection long before integrative medicine was mainstream. As a practicing physician, she quickly realized that a healthy self-image is a critical component of optimal health and was one of the first physicians to offer the full spectrum of health, wellness, and cosmetic procedures in her practice.
After over twenty years of success in Central Ohio, Dr. McQuillan relocated her practice to Florida, where she further intensified her commitment to individualized medicine by incorporating the healing power of a patient's own stem cells to treat various degenerative conditions. In conjunction with an international team of experts, she has authored over twenty clinical studies utilizing autologous stem cells to treat many common ailments.
Dr. McQuillan's passion for teaching, standardization, and superior patient outcomes led her to the formation of Ageless Health, a hands-on training company for medical professionals. Dr. McQuillan has educated thousands of her colleagues in the art and science of integrative, regenerative, and aesthetic medicine.
Some of Dr. McQuillan's prestigious titles include Medical Director of both the Aesthetic and Stem Cell and Regenerative Medicine Fellowships for the American Academy of Anti-Aging Medicine. Dr. McQuillan speaks internationally on the subjects of integrative, regenerative, and aesthetic medicine for many organizations and has been featured in numerous national and trade publications. She has appeared on Telemundo and Good Morning America and has made numerous local television appearances.
Her commitment to wellness beauty, and successful aging has expanded to other organizations as well. She currently serves as Medical Director for Great HealthWorks, a consumer-directed health and wellness product manufacturer and distributor. As Co-Executive Editor of New You Magazine and Chairman of the New You Medical Advisory Board, she educates the public responsibly in the best practices for successful aging. About:
Dr. Sarraga was born and raised in Puerto Rico, where he spent most of his life. Dr. Sarraga decided at a very early age to follow in his grandfather's footsteps and pursue a career in the art of medicine and surgery. Even before entering medical school, Dr. Sarraga was fascinated by surgery; he spent all his summers volunteering in the operating room at the Cardiovascular Center in Puerto Rico. After completing his undergraduate studies in Chicago, he attended medical school at the University of Puerto Rico, where he received many awards including membership in the prestigious Alpha Omega Alpha honor society and being in the top 10 percent of his class.
Dr. Sarraga then completed a full general surgery residency at the University of Puerto Rico, where he was recognized as intern of the year during his internship year. While training at the oncologic hospital, he was first exposed to breast reconstruction. Soon after he decided that plastic surgery was his calling. Dr. Sarraga felt that restoring a woman's sense of self after she had undergone a mastectomy operation by reconstructing her breasts was a vitally important part of her eventual complete "cure" and recovery process. During his last year, he was chosen among his peers as Administrative Chief Resident and soon afterwards became Board Certified in General Surgery.
Dr. Sarraga then went North to complete his plastic surgery residency at the prestigious University of Massachusetts in New England. During his last year of training he was again recognized as Administrative Chief Resident amongst his peers. During his plastic surgery residency, Dr. Sarraga trained with the top aesthetic plastic surgeons in Boston learning the most up to date techniques in Facial plastic surgery, rhinoplasty, body contouring and fat grafting.
Dr. Sarraga then became interested on the healing and reconstructive properties of human fat cells, and decided to pursue some extra training with experts in the developing field of fat grafting and fat transfers This included Dr. Daniel Delvecchio. Stemming from this interest, Dr. Sarraga did additional clinical research on fat grafting for reconstruction of the breast, a topic that he has presented several papers on at international meetings. After completing his residency Dr. Sarraga was nominated as Assistant Professor of Surgery in the Division of Plastic Surgery at the University of Massachusetts.
Fascinated by eyelid surgery and its complex anatomy and physiology, Dr. Sarraga then pursued a fellowship in Ophthalmic Plastic and Reconstructive Surgery with Dr. Pascale Perusse, a prominent surgeon with over 25 years of experience and an expert in the field. During this fellowship, he learned about the intricacies of oculoplastic surgery and rejuvenation of the upper face (eyelids, cheeks, brow).
Dr. Sarraga joined Dr. Storch in practice at the beginning of July 2012 here in sunny South Florida. He has been extensively mentored by Dr. Storch in Face, Neck and Rhinoplasty Cosmetic Surgery. He is very passionate about his work and strives to do exceptional work that will help his each patients improve their appearance and even, perhaps, the quality of their life. He regularly performs oculoplastic, facial rejuvenation (surgery of the face, neck and eyes), Rhinoplasty and cosmetic and reconstructive breast surgery. He is also a Ophthalmic Plastic Surgery consultant for various Ophthalmology practices from Miami to Fort Lauderdale and Weston. He is an active member of the prestigious American Society of Aesthetic Plastic Surgeons (ASAPS), the American Society of Plastic Surgeons (ASPS) and the Southeastern Society of Plastic and Reconstructive Surgeons (SESPRS).
